s 2D. Let me reconsider.\n    # \n    # The constraint is: cell at position (ax+i, ay+j) must equal cell at (ax+i+dx, ay+j+dy)\n    # for all valid (i,j) in [0,r-1]x[0,c-1].\n    # This creates a graph where we connect (i,j) to (i+dx, j+dy) if both are in range.\n    # \n    # Components: each connected component is a chain\n    # i: 0,1,...,r-1 with step dx\n    # j: 0,1,...,c-1 with step dy\n    # But i and j move together!\n    # \n    # So the chain from (i0, j0) is: (i0, j0), (i0+dx, j0+dy), (i0+2dx, j0+2dy), ...\n    # as long as in range.\n    # \n    # A point (i,j) is a chain start if (i-dx, j-dy) is not in [0,r-1]x[0,c-1].\n    # i.e., i-dx < 0 or i-dx >= r or j-dy < 0 or j-dy >= c\n    \n    # Count chain starts:\n    # Total (i,j) in [0,r-1]x[0,c-1] where (i-dx, j-dy) NOT in range\n    # = r*c - (number where (i-dx, j-dy) IS in range)\n    # (i-dx) in [0,r-1] means i in [dx, r-1+dx] intersect [0,r-1]\n    # (j-dy) in [0,c-1] means j in [dy, c-1+dy] intersect [0,c-1]\n    \n    if dx >= 0:\n        row_valid = max(0, r - dx)  # i in [dx, r-1]\n    else:\n        row_valid = max(0, r + dx)  # i in [0, r-1+dx]\n    \n    if dy >= 0:\n        col_valid = max(0, c - dy)\n    else:\n        col_valid = max(0, c + dy)\n    \n    # Number of (i,j) where predecessor is in range\n    pred_in_range = row_valid * col_valid\n    \n    # Number of chain starts\n    num_components_in_rect = r * c - pred_in_range\n    \n    # Free cells = cells outside union + components inside union\n    outside = n * m - union_size\n    exp = outside + num_components_in_rect\n    \n    print(pow(k, exp, MOD))\n\nsolve()",
